Sentencas: As anode-support materials for solid oxide fuel cells, porous LaNbO4-NiO-Y2O3 stabilized ZrO2 (YSZ) composites (LNY), containing 0, 5, 10, 15, and 20 wt% of LaNbO4 and designated as 0LNO, 5LNO, 10LNO, 15LNO, and 20LNO, respectively, are prepared by tape casting and sintering.
Titulo: LaNbO4-NiO-Y2O3 Stabilized ZrO2 Anode-Support Materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: They are investigated for their microstructure and mechanical, electrical and thermal expansion properties.
Titulo: LaNbO4-NiO-Y2O3 Stabilized ZrO2 Anode-Support Materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The porosity of as-sintered LNY is around 30%, and that of reduced LNY cermets decreases from 47% for reduced 0LNO to 43% for reduced 20LNO.
Titulo: LaNbO4-NiO-Y2O3 Stabilized ZrO2 Anode-Support Materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The fracture strength (sigma(f)) of LNY is higher than that of the reduced form; however, both of them are not rather sensitive to the amount of LaNbO4, depending on crack-originating flaws in the specimens.
Titulo: LaNbO4-NiO-Y2O3 Stabilized ZrO2 Anode-Support Materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The fracture toughness (K-IC) of LNY increases with LaNbO4 content and is 1.87 MPa.m(1/2) for 20LNO, which is more than 20% increase from that of 0LNO; however the K-IC for reduced LNY is higher than that of LNY, and decreases with increasing LaNbO4 content due to the decreased amount of ductile metallic Ni phase.
Titulo: LaNbO4-NiO-Y2O3 Stabilized ZrO2 Anode-Support Materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The conductivity of reduced LNY depends on Ni content and is higher than 289 S/cm at temperatures below 900 degrees C.
Titulo: LaNbO4-NiO-Y2O3 Stabilized ZrO2 Anode-Support Materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The coefficient of thermal expansion (CTE) of both LNY and reduced LNY is in the range between 12.4 and 11.4 x 10(-6) K-1; which is closely matched with that of YSZ electrolyte.
Titulo: LaNbO4-NiO-Y2O3 Stabilized ZrO2 Anode-Support Materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
